Direct incentive is "move later", for a miner to confirm the existing economic consensus, to avoid partitioning themselves away from it.

Miners have incentives to be followers of economic consensus, not leaders or deciders. Suicide to partition self away from income stream.
The exchanges are the real gateways / choke points of "economic consensus" in a fork. Not the miners.
It is theorized healthier to let the market decide, versus poor proxies such as exchanges (the heavyweights), miners, devs, online polls.
Long term, Agree w/ Meni Rosenfeld & (separately) @ Truthcoin that markets and wallets need automated forked-coin support, ETH'1 and ETH'2.
